  "riddle": "1. Seek the tale of the Ivorian guardian who safeguards the net, and reveal his day of birth to begin your quest.\n\n2. A talented player once dazzled the pitch in France; which years saw him don the colors of the club from Nantes?\n\n3. In a year of continental strife, how many squads took to the field in the prestigious tournament of African champions?\n\n4. Elevation matters; how high above sea level does the ground rest beneath the competitors of a Pan American gathering?\n\n5. A new chapter awaits in a fierce battle of African clubs; how many teams partook in this second-tier tournament?\n\n6. Unveil the greatest prime factor of that count — what prime number reigns supreme among them?\n\n7. Explore the waters of a district founded in the shadow of a famous bridge; what numerical coordinates pinpoint this vibrant locale?\n\n8. Where do the cobblestones meet the spirit of the West Coast? Ascertain the height at which this historic area thrives.\n\n9. How many places offering rest nestle near the heart of this charming district you’ve discovered?\n\n10. From your findings in clues 8 and 9, combine those results to unveil a new number representative of the landscape.\n\n11. As you wander the streets of a historic neighborhood in the City of Angels, how many healing sanctuaries lie within easy reach?\n\n12. Reduce your count from clue 11 to a single digit — what is the essence that emerges from this iterative sum?\n\n13. The coordinates of a public square, vibrant with life, hold your next answer — what are they?\n\n14. In a vibrant Irish locale known for its railways, which year marked the rejuvenation of a key interchange?\n\n15. Search for the elevation of that same railway haven — how far above the world does it rise? \n\n16. Count the lush green escapes near this railway station; how many tranquil parks greet visitors nearby?\n\n17. Combine the height of that railway station with the number of parks found in the area from clues 15 and 16 to reveal a significant difference.\n\n18. Roaming through the land of the maple leaf, what number represents its vibrant population?\n\n19. Now, harness your abilities to compute: from the values collected in clues 4, 10, and 11, calculate the expression: abs(259 - 10) % 10. Your result will be a single digit, a final key to your journey.",
